ed":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/spec.md","time":{"start":1775886177205,"end":1775886177232}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886177236,"sessionID":"ses_284efaa0cffezmUnwinR9j3L9E","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1087a2001qSmUleHC4q5Jot","messageID":"msg_d7b10717f001KjuZvNqcokgyJM","sessionID":"ses_284efaa0cffezmUnwinR9j3L9E","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-65d8c65e9a7443739aff919775866c67","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 вҖ” Dockerfile еӨҡйҳ¶ж®өжһ„е»ә (3 images)\n2: \n3: ## жҰӮиҝ°\n4: \n5: | еұһжҖ§ | еҖј |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-032 |\n8: | Module | docker |\n9: | Language | Dockerfile |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (зӣ®зҡ„)\n15: \n16: Define multi-stage Dockerfile patterns for AgentCube's three core container images, optimizing for:\n17: \n18: 1. **Build Separation**: Isolate Go compilation (builder stage) from runtime environment to reduce final image size\n19: 2. **Security**: Run containers as non-root users with minimal runtime dependencies\n20: 3. **Build Efficiency**: Leverage BuildKit cache mounts for Go module downloads to accelerate CI builds\n21: 4. **Consistency**: Standardize Dockerfile structure across workloadmanager, router, and picod images\n22: \n23: **Target Images**:\n24: \n25: | Image | Binary | Runtime Base | User |\n26: |-------|--------|--------------|------|\n27: | `workloadmanager` | `./cmd/workload-manager` | `alpine:3.19` | `apiserver` (UID 1000) |\n28: | `agentcube-router` | `./cmd/router` | `alpine:3.19` | `router` (UID 1000) |\n29: | `picod` | `./cmd/picod` | `ubuntu:24.04` | `root` (sandbox permissions) |\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. Scope (иҢғеӣҙ)\n34: \n35: ### 2.1 In Scope\n36: \n37: | Deliverable | Description |\n38: |-------------|-------------|\n39: | `docker/Dockerfile` | Multi-stage build for Workload Manager (builder вҶ’ runtime) |\n40: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Multi-stage build for Router (builder вҶ’ runtime) |\n41: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Multi-stage build for PicoD (builder вҶ’ runtime) |\n42: | `Makefile docker-* targets` | Build targets referencing Dockerfiles (already exist) |\n43: | Build args documentation | `TARGETOS`, `TARGETARCH` platform args for cross-compilation |\n44: \n45: ### 2.2 Dockerfile Stage Structure\n46: \n47: **Workload Manager / Router (2-stage)**:\n48: \n49: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n50: |-------|------|---------|\n51: | `builder` | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | Go compilation with BuildKit cache mounts |\n52: | `runtime` | `alpine:3.19` | Minimal runtime with ca-certificates, non-root user |\n53: \n54: **PicoD (2-stage)**:\n55: \n56: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n57: |-------|------|---------|\n58: | `builder` | `golang:1.24.4` | Go compilation |\n59: | `runtime` | `ubuntu:24.04` | Python3 dependency for sandbox execution, runs as root |\n60: \n61: ### 2.3 Out of Scope\n62: \n63: | Item | Reason |\n64: |------|--------|\n65: | Multi-arch buildx configuration | Covered by existing `docker-buildx-*` Make targets |\n66: | Docker registry push logic | Covered by `docker-buildx-push-*` targets and CI workflow |\n67: | Helm chart image references | Chart values already reference correct image names |\n68: | Volcano scheduler image | Separate component with external image repository |\n69: | Distroless base images | Alpine/Ubuntu provide sufficient minimal runtime; distroless migration is separate AR |\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## 3. Impact Analysis (еҪұе“ҚеҲҶжһҗ)\n74: \n75: ### 3.1 ж–°еўһж–Үд»¶\n76: \n77: | File | Description |\n78: |------|-------------|\n79: | N/A | Dockerfiles already exist in `docker/` directory |\n80: \n81: ### 3.2 дҝ®ж”№ж–Үд»¶\n82: \n83: | File | Change |\n84: |------|--------|\n85: | `docker/Dockerfile` | Validate existing multi-stage pattern; add BuildKit cache mount optimization |\n86: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Add `COPY client-go/ client-go/` for Go module dependencies; validate cache mounts |\n87: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Validate builder вҶ’ runtime stage separation; document root user requirement |\n88: | `Makefile` | Ensure `docker-build-*` targets pass correct build args (`TARGETOS`, `TARGETARCH`) |\n89: \n90: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n91: \n92: | Dependency | Purpose |\n93: |------------|---------|\n94: | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | Builder stage base image for Go compilation |\n95: | `golang:1.24.4` | Builder stage base for picod (matches Go version in CI) |\n96: | `alpine:3.19` | Minimal runtime base for workloadmanager/router |\n97: | `ubuntu:24.04` | Runtime base for picod (requires Python3 for sandbox) |\n98: | `ca-certificates` | TLS certificate bundle for HTTPS connections |\n99: \n100: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n101: \n102: | Consumer | Usage |\n103: |----------|-------|\n104: | `CI: main.yml` | `make docker-build` builds workloadmanager image |\n105: | `CI: build-push-release.yml` | `make docker-buildx-push-*` pushes multi-arch images to ghcr.io |\n106: | `E2E: run_e2e.sh` | `make docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` for Kind cluster |\n107: | `Helm chart` | References images by `repository:tag` from values.yaml |\n108: | `Kind cluster` | `kind load docker-image` loads local images for E2E testing |\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (еӨҮйҖүж–№жЎҲ)\n113: \n114: ### Alternative 1: Single-stage Dockerfile (no builder separation)\n115: \n116: **Approach**: Build Go binary directly in runtime base image.\n117: \n118: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n119: |--------|------------|\n120: | Pros | Simpler Dockerfile; fewer stages |\n121: | Cons | Final image includes Go toolchain (~300MB); larger attack surface; slower image pulls |\n122: \n123: **Decision**: Rejected. Multi-stage builds produce minimal runtime images (~20MB for Alpine-based) by excluding compiler and build dependencies.\n124: \n125: ### Alternative 2: Distroless base images (gcr.io/distroless/static)\n126: \n127: **Approach**: Use distroless/static or distroless/base for runtime stage.\n128: \n129: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n130: |--------|------------|\n131: | Pros | Smallest possible image; no shell/package manager; enhanced security |\n132: | Cons | Debugging harder (no shell); requires separate debug image for troubleshooting; picod needs Python3 (distroless/static insufficient) |\n133: \n134: **Decision**: Rejected for current scope. Alpine provides minimal footprint with shell for debugging. Distroless migration should be separate AR with debug image strategy.\n135: \n136: ### Alternative 3: Shared builder stage via Dockerfile inheritance\n137: \n138: **Approach**: Create base builder Dockerfile and `FROM` it in component Dockerfiles.\n139: \n140: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n141: |--------|------------|\n142: | Pros | Reduced duplication; centralized Go version management |\n143: | Cons | Dockerfile inheritance limited; BuildKit cache mounts require explicit declaration; additional base image build step |\n144: \n145: **Decision**: Rejected. Each Dockerfile should be self-contained for CI simplicity. Go version consistency managed via Makefile variables and CI workflow Go version pins.\n146: \n147: ### Alternative 4: Static binary compilation with musl libc\n148: \n149: **Approach**: Compile with `-tags netgo,osusergo` for fully static binaries, use scratch base image.\n150: \n151: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n152: |--------|------------|\n153: | Pros | Zero-dependency runtime; smallest image size; no libc version issues |\n154: | Cons | DNS resolution requires netgo tag; Go modules with CGO disabled; picod requires Python3 dependency |\n155: \n156: **Decision**: Partially adopted. `CGO_ENABLED=0` already used; Alpine (musl libc) provides static-like behavior without scratch complexity. Fully static binaries with scratch reserved for future optimization.\n157: \n158: ### Alternative 5: Pre-built binary COPY (no in-container compilation)\n159: \n160: **Approach**: Build binaries outside Docker, COPY into runtime stage.\n161: \n162: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n163: |--------|------------|\n164: | Pros | Faster builds if binaries cached; no Go image dependency |\n165: | Cons | Requires host Go toolchain matching target platform; CI complexity for cross-arch builds; reproducibility harder to guarantee |\n166: \n167: **Decision**: Rejected. In-container compilation ensures consistent build environment, handles cross-platform compilation via `TARGETOS/TARGETARCH`, and leverages BuildKit layer caching.\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## 5. Risks\n172: \n173: | Risk | Mitigation |\n174: |------|------------|\n175: | Go version drift (builder vs CI) | CI workflow pins Go 1.24.4/1.24.9; Makefile docker targets align with Dockerfile base images |\n176: | Alpine libc DNS issues | Use `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static-like compilation; ca-certificates installed for TLS |\n177: | PicoD root user security | Documented requirement for sandbox permissions; sandbox pods isolate picod from host |\n178: | BuildKit cache invalidation | `go mod download` cache mount keyed by `go.mod/go.sum` hash; CI uses Buildx with cache export |\n179: | Image size bloat | Multi-stage ensures only binary copied to runtime; Alpine base ~5MB overhead |\n180: | Cross-arch build failures | Makefile `docker-buildx` targets use `--platform linux/amd64,arm64` with `TARGETOS/TARGETARCH` args |\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n185: \n186: - [ ] Validate `docker/Dockerfile` multi-stage structure (builder вҶ’ runtime)\n187: - [ ] Validate `docker/Dockerfile.router` includes `COPY client-go/ client-go/`\n188: - [ ] Validate `docker/Dockerfile.picod` uses `ubuntu:24.04` runtime with Python3\n189: - [ ] Verify BuildKit cache mounts: `--mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod`\n190: - [ ] Verify `CGO_ENABLED=0` in build command\n191: - [ ] Verify non-root user in workloadmanager/router runtime stages\n192: - [ ] Test `make docker-build` produces <50MB runtime image\n193: - [ ] Test `make docker-build-router` produces <50MB runtime image\n194: - [ ] Test `make docker-build-picod` produces functional image\n195: - [ ] Verify `TARGETOS=linux TARGETARCH=amd64` produces correct binary\n196: - [ ] Verify `TARGETOS=linux TARGETARCH=arm64` cross-compilation works\n197: - [ ] E2E test: `kind load docker-image` succeeds for all 3 images\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## 7. References\n202: \n203: - Docker multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/\n204: - BuildKit cache mounts: https://docs.docker.com/build/buildkit/#cache-mounts\n205: - Go cross-compilation: https://go.dev/doc/install/source#environment\n206: - deployment/design.md вҖ” Dockerfiles section (lines 157-178)\n207: - ci-cd/design.md вҖ” Build targets and CI workflow (lines 173-179)\n208: - deployment/spec.md вҖ” Docker images requirement (line 77-83)\n209: - manifests/charts/base/values.yaml вҖ” Image repository/tag defaults\n\n(End of file - total 209 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 вҖ” Dockerfile еӨҡйҳ¶ж®өжһ„е»ә (3 images)\n\n## жҰӮиҝ°\n\n| еұһжҖ§ | еҖј |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-032 |\n| Module | docker |\n| Language | Dockerfile |\n| Size | S |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (зӣ®зҡ„)\n\nDefine multi-stage Dockerfile patterns for AgentCube's three core container images, optimizing for:\n\n1. **Build Separation**: Isolate Go compilation (builder stage) from runtime environment to reduce final image size\n2. **Security**: Run containers as non-root users with minimal runtime dependencies\n3. **Build Efficiency**: Leverage BuildKit cache mounts for Go module downloads to accelerate CI builds","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775886177202,"end":1775886177234}}}}
