{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886191989,"sessionID":"ses_284efaa0cffezmUnwinR9j3L9E","part":{"id":"prt_d7b10c95100162rapzFYjvTn7j","messageID":"msg_d7b10af1c001SJ8TOZ4YZodZBD","sessionID":"ses_284efaa0cffezmUnwinR9j3L9E","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8bb39fdc107845ddaf4b0dd0f6d115f5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-032 вҖ” Dockerfile еӨҡйҳ¶ж®өжһ„е»ә\n2: \n3: **Module:** `docker`  \n4: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define multi-stage Dockerfiles for three AgentCube images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`). Each uses a builder stage for Go compilation and a runtime stage with Alpine 3.19 running as non-root user.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Workload Manager Dockerfile multi-stage build\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a multi-stage Dockerfile at `docker/Dockerfile` that compiles the Workload Manager Go binary and packages it in a minimal Alpine runtime image.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Builder stage uses Go 1.24\n22: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` exists\n23: - **WHEN** the first `FROM` instruction is examined\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.24-alpine` as the builder base image\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Builder stage sets CGO_ENABLED=0\n27: - **GIVEN** the builder stage in `docker/Dockerfile`\n28: - **WHEN** build environment is configured\n29: - **THEN** `ENV CGO_ENABLED=0` SHALL be set for static binary compilation\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Builder stage copies Go source\n32: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n33: - **WHEN** source files are prepared\n34: - **THEN** `WORKDIR /app` SHALL be set\n35: - **AND** `COPY . .` SHALL copy repository contents to `/app`\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Builder stage compiles workloadmanager binary\n38: - **GIVEN** the builder stage with source copied\n39: - **WHEN** `RUN go build` is executed\n40: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/workload-manager` with `-o /app/bin/workloadmanager`\n41: - **AND** flags SHALL include `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n44: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` second stage\n45: - **WHEN** the runtime `FROM` instruction is examined\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as the base image\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Runtime stage creates non-root user\n49: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n50: - **WHEN** user setup is executed\n51: - **THEN** `RUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver` SHALL create user `apiserver` with UID 1000\n52: - **AND** `USER 1000` SHALL switch to non-root execution\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: Runtime stage copies binary from builder\n55: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n56: - **WHEN** binary is copied\n57: - **THEN** `COPY --from=builder /app/bin/workloadmanager /app/bin/workloadmanager` SHALL copy the compiled binary\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Runtime stage exposes port 8080\n60: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n61: - **WHEN** port configuration is examined\n62: - **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Runtime stage sets entrypoint\n65: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n66: - **WHEN** container startup is configured\n67: - **THEN** `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/workloadmanager\"]` SHALL be set\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### Requirement: Router Dockerfile multi-stage build\n72: \n73: The system SHALL provide a multi-stage Dockerfile at `docker/Dockerfile.router` that compiles the Router Go binary and packages it in a minimal Alpine runtime image.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Router builder stage uses Go 1.24\n76: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` exists\n77: - **WHEN** the first `FROM` instruction is examined\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.24-alpine` as the builder base image\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Router builder stage sets CGO_ENABLED=0\n81: - **GIVEN** the builder stage in `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n82: - **WHEN** build environment is configured\n83: - **THEN** `ENV CGO_ENABLED=0` SHALL be set for static binary compilation\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Router builder stage copies Go source\n86: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n87: - **WHEN** source files are prepared\n88: - **THEN** `WORKDIR /app` SHALL be set\n89: - **AND** `COPY . .` SHALL copy repository contents to `/app`\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Router builder stage compiles router binary\n92: - **GIVEN** the builder stage with source copied\n93: - **WHEN** `RUN go build` is executed\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/router` with `-o /app/bin/router`\n95: - **AND** flags SHALL include `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Router runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n98: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` second stage\n99: - **WHEN** the runtime `FROM` instruction is examined\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as the base image\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Router runtime stage creates non-root user\n103: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n104: - **WHEN** user setup is executed\n105: - **THEN** `RUN adduser -D -u 1000 router` SHALL create user `router` with UID 1000\n106: - **AND** `USER 1000` SHALL switch to non-root execution\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Router runtime stage copies binary from builder\n109: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n110: - **WHEN** binary is copied\n111: - **THEN** `COPY --from=builder /app/bin/router /app/bin/router` SHALL copy the compiled binary\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Router runtime stage exposes port 8080\n114: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n115: - **WHEN** port configuration is examined\n116: - **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Router runtime stage sets entrypoint\n119: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n120: - **WHEN** container startup is configured\n121: - **THEN** `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/router\"]` SHALL be set\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: picod Dockerfile multi-stage build\n126: \n127: The system SHALL provide a multi-stage Dockerfile at `docker/Dockerfile.picod` that compiles the picod Go binary and packages it in a minimal Alpine runtime image.\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: picod builder stage uses Go 1.24\n130: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` exists\n131: - **WHEN** the first `FROM` instruction is examined\n132: - **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.24-alpine` as the builder base image\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: picod builder stage sets CGO_ENABLED=0\n135: - **GIVEN** the builder stage in `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n136: - **WHEN** build environment is configured\n137: - **THEN** `ENV CGO_ENABLED=0` SHALL be set for static binary compilation\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: picod builder stage copies Go source\n140: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n141: - **WHEN** source files are prepared\n142: - **THEN** `WORKDIR /app` SHALL be set\n143: - **AND** `COPY . .` SHALL copy repository contents to `/app`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: picod builder stage compiles picod binary\n146: - **GIVEN** the builder stage with source copied\n147: - **WHEN** `RUN go build` is executed\n148: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/picod` with `-o /app/bin/picod`\n149: - **AND** flags SHALL include `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: picod runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n152: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` second stage\n153: - **WHEN** the runtime `FROM` instruction is examined\n154: - **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as the base image\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: picod runtime stage creates non-root user\n157: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n158: - **WHEN** user setup is executed\n159: - **THEN** `RUN adduser -D -u 1000 picod` SHALL create user `picod` with UID 1000\n160: - **AND** `USER 1000` SHALL switch to non-root execution\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: picod runtime stage copies binary from builder\n163: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n164: - **WHEN** binary is copied\n165: - **THEN** `COPY --from=builder /app/bin/picod /app/bin/picod` SHALL copy the compiled binary\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: picod runtime stage exposes port 8080\n168: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n169: - **WHEN** port configuration is examined\n170: - **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: picod runtime stage sets entrypoint\n173: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n174: - **WHEN** container startup is configured\n175: - **THEN** `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/picod\"]` SHALL be set\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### Requirement: Dockerfile build execution\n180: \n181: The system SHALL produce working container images when Dockerfiles are built with repository root as context.\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image builds successfully\n184: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n185: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t agentcube-workloadmanager .` is executed\n186: - **THEN** the build SHALL complete without errors\n187: - **AND** the image SHALL contain `/app/bin/workloadmanager` binary\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Router image builds successfully\n190: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n191: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router .` is executed\n192: - **THEN** the build SHALL complete without errors\n193: - **AND** the image SHALL contain `/app/bin/router` binary\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: picod image builds successfully\n196: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n197: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod -t agentcube-picod .` is executed\n198: - **THEN** the build SHALL complete without errors\n199: - **AND** the image SHALL contain `/app/bin/picod` binary\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Images run as non-root user\n202: - **GIVEN** Workload Manager, Router, or picod images built\n203: - **WHEN** container is started and process inspected\n204: - **THEN** the running process SHALL NOT be root (UID 0)\n205: - **AND** process SHALL run as UID 1000\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ### Requirement: Makefile docker build targets\n210: \n211: The system SHALL provide Makefile targets for building Docker images.\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Makefile docker-build target for Workload Manager\n214: - **GIVEN** `Makefile` exists\n215: - **WHEN** `make docker-build` is executed\n216: - **THEN** it SHALL build Workload Manager image using `docker/Dockerfile`\n217: - **AND** image tag SHALL follow pattern `$(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION)`\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Makefile docker-build-router target\n220: - **GIVEN** `Makefile` exists\n221: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` is executed\n222: - **THEN** it SHALL build Router image using `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n223: - **AND** image tag SHALL follow pattern `$(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION)`\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Makefile docker-build-picod target\n226: - **GIVEN** `Makefile` exists\n227: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` is executed\n228: - **THEN** it SHALL build picod image using `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n229: - **AND** image tag SHALL follow pattern `$(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION)`\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: Makefile docker-build-all target\n232: - **GIVEN** `Makefile` exists\n233: - **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` is executed\n234: - **THEN** it SHALL build all three images (workloadmanager, router, picod) in sequence\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ### Requirement: Image size optimization\n239: \n240: The system SHALL produce minimal runtime images by excluding build tools and intermediate files.\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Runtime image excludes Go toolchain\n243: - **GIVEN** built Workload Manager image\n244: - **WHEN** image contents are inspected\n245: - **THEN** the image SHALL NOT contain Go compiler or SDK files\n246: - **AND** only the compiled binary and minimal Alpine runtime SHALL be present\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Runtime image excludes source code\n249: - **GIVEN** built Router image\n250: - **WHEN** image contents are inspected\n251: - **THEN** the image SHALL NOT contain Go source files (*.go)\n252: - **AND** only the compiled binary SHALL be present under `/app/bin/`\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Binary is optimized with stripped symbols\n255: - **GIVEN** built picod binary in image\n256: - **WHEN** binary size is inspected\n257: - **THEN** `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` SHALL strip DWARF debug info and symbol table\n258: - **AND** binary size SHALL be minimized compared to unstripped build\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## Constants Summary\n263: \n264: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n265: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n266: | `GO_VERSION` | `1.24` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Go builder image version |\n267: | `ALPINE_VERSION` | `3.19` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Runtime base image version |\n268: | `RUNTIME_UID` | `1000` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Non-root user UID for security |\n269: | `EXPOSE_PORT` | `8080` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | HTTP service port |\n270: | `BINARY_OUTPUT_DIR` | `/app/bin` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Binary location in both stages |\n271: | `LD_FLAGS` | `-w -s` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Strip debug/symbol for size optimization |\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## Dependencies Summary\n276: \n277: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n278: |---------|---------|---------|\n279: | `golang` | `1.24-alpine` | Go builder image with Alpine base |\n280: | `alpine` | `3.19` | Minimal runtime base image |\n281: | `Docker` | `>=20.10` | Multi-stage build support |\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## File Changes Summary\n286: \n287: | File | Action | Description |\n288: |------|--------|-------------|\n289: | `docker/Dockerfile` | Create | Workload Manager multi-stage build |\n290: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Create | Router multi-stage build |\n291: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Create | picod multi-stage build |\n292: | `Makefile` | Modify | Add `docker-build-*` and `docker-build-all` targets |\n293: \n294: ---\n295: \n296: ## References\n297: \n298: - proposal.md вҖ” AR-032 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n299: - deployment/spec.md вҖ” Deployment specification with image requirements\n300: - project.md вҖ” AgentCube tech stack (Go 1.24, Alpine, multi-stage Docker)\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## Validation Checklist\n305: \n306: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile` exists with two-stage build structure\n307: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.router` exists with two-stage build structure\n308: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.picod` exists with two-stage build structure\n309: - [ ] All Dockerfiles use `golang:1.24-alpine` builder stage\n310: - [ ] All Dockerfiles use `alpine:3.19` runtime stage\n311: - [ ] All Dockerfiles set `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static compilation\n312: - [ ] All Dockerfiles create non-root user with UID 1000\n313: - [ ] All Dockerfiles expose port 8080\n314: - [ ] `make docker-build-all` builds all three images successfully\n315: - [ ] Built images run processes as UID 1000 (non-root)\n316: - [ ] Runtime images exclude Go toolchain and source files\n\n(End of file - total 316 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-032 вҖ” Dockerfile еӨҡйҳ¶ж®өжһ„е»ә\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine multi-stage Dockerfiles for three AgentCube images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`). Each uses a builder stage for Go compilation and a runtime stage with Alpine 3.19 running as non-root user.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Workload Manager Dockerfile multi-stage build\n\nThe system SHALL provide a multi-stage Dockerfile at `docker/Dockerfile` that compiles the Workload Manager Go binary and packages it in a minimal Alpine runtime image.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775886191977,"end":1775886191987}}}}
